gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Hawks 127, Timberwolves 113
gameRecap.excerpt: Atlanta outscored Minnesota, 67-34 in the second half on their way to a 127-113 victory. Dejounte Murray scored 30 of his 41 total points in the 2nd half (12-14 FG in the 2nd half), to go along with seven rebounds and five assists overall. Trae Young added 24 points and eight assists as DeAndre Hunter totaled 16 points, four rebounds, and two assists for Atlanta. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 31 points, seven assists, and six rebounds. The Hawks improve to 2-2 as the Timberwolves fall to 1-2.
